To get metadata to send to Marist SSO admin:

Set Up Your Web Server:

Ensure your web server (e.g., IIS on Windows or Apache on Linux) is installed and configured to serve your application.
Install Shibboleth SP:

Install the Shibboleth SP software on your server.
Configure Shibboleth SP:

Ensure your shibboleth2.xml file is correctly configured with the necessary paths and settings.
Enable HTTPS:

Ensure your web server is configured to use HTTPS, as the metadata URL must be accessed over HTTPS.
Start the Shibboleth SP Service:

Ensure the Shibboleth SP service is running.



Apache config:
Install Apache:
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install apache2

Install Shibboleth SP:
sudo apt-get install libapache2-mod-shib2

Configure Apache:

Edit your Apache configuration file (e.g., /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf):

<VirtualHost *:443>
    ServerName your.sp.example.com
    DocumentRoot /var/www/html

    SSLEngine on
    SSLCertificateFile /path/to/your/certificate.crt
    SSLCertificateKeyFile /path/to/your/private.key

    <Location /secure>
        AuthType shibboleth
        ShibRequestSetting requireSession 1
        require valid-user
    </Location>

    <Location /Shibboleth.sso>
        SetHandler shib
    </Location>

    ShibRequestSetting applicationId default
    ShibRequestSetting requireSession 1
</VirtualHost>

Enable the SSL module and site configuration:
sudo a2enmod ssl
sudo a2ensite default-ssl
sudo systemctl restart apache2

Restart Shibboleth SP Service:
sudo systemctl restart shibd

Generate Metadata
Once your web server and Shibboleth SP are set up and running, you can generate the metadata by accessing the following URL in your web browser:
https://your.sp.example.com/Shibboleth.sso/Metadata